properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 8:28PM CST until February 13 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW AND WIND ALONG WITH MUCH COLDER TEMPERATURES OVERNIGHT...

.An arctic cold front continues to push southward across the area
this evening, bringing light snow and wind along with much colder
temperatures. 1 to 3 inches of snow is expected across east-
central Wisconsin. Less than an inch of additional accumulation is
expected across the north, except locally higher amounts across
the snowbelt region of northwest Vilas County.

Gusty northerly winds of 15 to 25 mph, except 20 to 30 mph with
gusts around 35 mph across the Fox Valley east to the lakeshore
will create areas of blowing and drifting snow into early Thursday
morning. Temperatures falling well below freezing may lead to a
flash freeze, leading to the potential for black ice.

The combination of cold temperatures and winds will result in
wind chills as low as 20 below to 25 below zero over north
central and parts of central Wisconsin late tonight into Thursday
morning.

Motorists should anticipate hazardous travel conditions tonight,
especially in the Fox Valley and lakeshore areas. Anyone planning
outdoor activities should dress in layers and cover exposed skin
to avoid the risk of frostbite.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches.
Winds gusting to around 35 mph, causing areas of blowing and
drifting snow. Rapidly falling temperatures may cause wet roads
to flash freeze, leading to areas of black ice.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on hazardous travel conditions, with snow or ice
covered roads. Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility in open areas, especially on west to east oriented
roads.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Wisconsin can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST THURSDAY
